### Hello! I will ask you a few questions (around 4) about your data ecosystem. At the end, you will get recommendations and suggested courses of action.

- Onepoint’s Data & Analytics Body of Knowledge is the basis for the diagnostics and recommendations.
- If you’d like, you can ask for a copy of the results to be emailed to you.
- This is an experimental tool. Any feedback and improvement ideas are always welcome — thank you!
Let’s get started.

### Which area of your data ecosystem are you most concerned about? The table below may help with your response — it captures some of the most common data and analytics challenges our clients face.
Poor data quality - Low-quality data can lead to incorrect insights and poor decision-making.
Compliance and security risks - Mishandling data can lead to legal troubles and reputational damage.
Data silos - Data trapped in departmental silos can be inaccessible to other parts.
Lack of skilled personnel - Missing skills in data science, analytics, AI and ML can impede the effective use of data.
Data overload - "Data glut" can slow down processes and make it difficult to identify what data is actually useful.
Cost and complexity - A robust data analytics infrastructure requires significant investment of resources.
Inconsistent data strategies - Difficult to align with modern concepts like Data Fabric, Mesh and Generative AI.
Resistance to change - Employees need to adapt to new ways of operating to make data-driven transformation work.
Poor data quality - Low-quality data can lead to incorrect insights and poor decision-making.
